text:
Archer Ave., west from Sutphin Boulevard to 138th Place, showing in the foreground, at the S.W. corner of the first two mentioned Streets the four story Long Island Railroad station. It is erected on the former Kissam farm.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Sutphin Boulevard, east side, north from Archer to Jamaica Aves. (elevated structure thereon).

October 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Archer Avenue, north side, east from Sutphin Boulevard, showing the physical character of this area as seen from the Long Island Railroad station at the corner of the two thoroughfares. Shown, too, are the Long Island Railroad tracks.

1925

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
